{
  "stem": "6076.8",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And a few weeks later, we got married.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That means in six weeks' time, we both got married.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I'm grateful and I'm happy to be together and live with my husband.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We should only live together.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I have two wonderful sons.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We traveled.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We hustled.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Three months later after we got married, we traveled to Wald-- Waldenburg, to Ulm.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went from place to place with the Hagganah took us out from the Russian-- from Lodz, you know?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We went away.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't want to stay with the Russians.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We wanted to be and the-- with the Americans on the American side.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Many, many survivors did the same thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They followed the same step.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Once [INAUDIBLE] followed the other.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Until we reached Augsburg because we find out that Herb had a brother who immigr-- who came from also from Germany, you know, a few weeks, a few months, a few weeks later than we.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he established already.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He found an apartment in Augsburg and his tante, his aunt and uncle, with their son.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I felt that I have a little family through him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And me and Tobcha, of course, we never separate.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I went with Tobcha.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, Tobcha remarried in Lodz with-- she find her right man, Joel, whom I brought him to her to-- he was-- he survived the partisans.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he lost his wife with a six-month-old baby.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's a long story to tell, but I have to make it in short.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he-- when I met him in the committee, I met him like, like a brother, he came to me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was a neighbor of ours from Wachock.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when I told him Tobcha survived, he was so excited.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
